In [6]:
def to_patches(images, masks):
    image_patches = []
    mask_patches = []
    for img in images:
        img = img/255
        image_patches.append(view_as_blocks(img, (64, 64, 32)))
    for msk in masks:
        # Normalize to 0 or 1
        if msk.max() != 0:
            msk = msk / msk.max()
        mask_patches.append(view_as_blocks(msk, (64, 64, 32)))
    image_patches = np.reshape(image_patches, (-1, 64, 64, 32))
    mask_patches = np.reshape(mask_patches, (-1, 64, 64, 32))
    return image_patches, mask_patches
        
def patches_to_img(patches):
    temp = np.reshape(patches, (4, 4, 4, 64, 64, 32))
    end = unpatchify(temp, (256, 256, 128))
    return end

y1_ones = [] # holds the ivcf patches in y_train

x2_zeros = [] # Same as above but for testing set
x2_ones = []

y2_zeros = []
y2_ones = []

for index in range(np.asarray(x1_patches).shape[0]):
    if y1_patches[index].max() == 1:
        x1_ones.append(x1_patches[index])

In [21]:
#This has identity mapping
def identity_block(input, num_filters, decode = False):
    x = Conv3D(num_filters, 3, padding="same")(input)
    x = BatchNormalization()(x)   #Not in the original network. 
    x = Activation("relu")(x)

    x = Conv3D(num_filters, 3, padding="same")(x)
    x = BatchNormalization()(x)  #Not in the original network
    x = Add()([x, input])
    x = Activation("relu")(x)

    return x

def conv_block(input, num_filters):
    x = Conv3D(num_filters, 3, strides=(2, 2, 2), padding="same")(input)
    x = BatchNormalization()(x)   #Not in the original network. 
    x = Activation("relu")(x)

    x = Conv3D(num_filters, 3, padding="same")(x)
    x = BatchNormalization()(x)  #Not in the original network
    # Processing Residue with conv(1,1)
    x_skip = Conv3D(num_filters, 3, strides=(2, 2, 2), padding = "same")(input)
    x = Add()([x, x_skip])
    x = Activation("relu")(x)
    
    return x

#Encoder block: Replace maxpooling with conv resnet blocks
def res_encoder_block(input, num_filters):
    x = identity_block(input, num_filters)
    x = identity_block(x, num_filters)
    p = conv_block(x, num_filters*2)
    
    return x, p   

#Decoder block
#skip features gets input from encoder for concatenation
def decoder_block(input, skip_features, num_filters):
    x = Conv3DTranspose(num_filters, (2, 2, 2), strides=2, padding="same")(input)
    x = Concatenate()([x, skip_features])
    x = Conv3D(num_filters, 3, padding="same")(x)
    x = identity_block(x, num_filters)
    return x

#Build Unet using the blocks
def build_resunet(input_shape, n_classes):
    inputs = Input(input_shape)
    
    s1, p1 = res_encoder_block(inputs, 32)
    s2, p2 = res_encoder_block(p1, 64)

    s3, p3 = res_encoder_block(p2, 128)
    s4, p4 = res_encoder_block(p3, 256)

    b1 = identity_block(p4, 512) #Bridge

    d1 = decoder_block(b1, s4, 256)
    d2 = decoder_block(d1, s3, 128)
    d3 = decoder_block(d2, s2, 64)
    d4 = decoder_block(d3, s1, 32)

    if n_classes == 1:  #Binary
        activation = 'sigmoid'
    else:
        activation = 'softmax'

    outputs = Conv3D(n_classes, 1, padding="same", activation=activation)(d4)  #Change the activation based on n_classes

    model = Model(inputs, outputs, name="ResUNet")
    return model

METRICS = [
      tf.keras.metrics.TruePositives(name='tp'),
      tf.keras.metrics.FalsePositives(name='fp'),
      tf.keras.metrics.TrueNegatives(name='tn'),
      tf.keras.metrics.FalseNegatives(name='fn'), 
      tf.keras.metrics.BinaryAccuracy(name='accuracy'),
      tf.keras.metrics.Precision(name='precision'),
      tf.keras.metrics.Recall(name='recall'),
      tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='auc'),
      tf.keras.metrics.AUC(name='prc', curve='PR'), # precision-recall curve
      tf.keras.metrics.OneHotMeanIoU(num_classes=2, name = 'mean_dice'),
      tf.keras.metrics.OneHotIoU(num_classes=2, target_class_ids=[0], name = 'normal_dice'),
      tf.keras.metrics.OneHotIoU(num_classes=2, target_class_ids=[1], name = 'ivc_dice')

  #######################################################################


def random_crop(input_image, input_label):
    seed = np.random.randint(10, 50)
    cropped_inputs = tf.image.random_crop(input_image, 
                                            size=[64, 64, 32], 
                                            seed=seed)
      
    cropped_labels = tf.image.random_crop(input_label,
                                            size=[64, 64, 32],
                                            seed=seed)
      
    return cropped_inputs, cropped_labels




# @tf.function()
def random_jitter(input_image, input_label):
    
#     input_label = tf.squeeze(input_label, axis=-1)
    
    new_w = int(1.1*64)
    new_h = int(1.1*64)
    
    input_image = tf.image.resize(input_image, [new_w, new_h],
                                  method=tf.image.ResizeMethod.BILINEAR)
    input_label = tf.image.resize(input_label, [new_w, new_h],
                                 method=tf.image.ResizeMethod.NEAREST_NEIGHBOR)
    
    # Random cropping back to 256x256
    input_image, input_label = random_crop(input_image, input_label)
  
    if tf.random.uniform(()) > 0.5:
      # Random mirroring
        input_image = tf.image.flip_left_right(input_image)
        input_label = tf.image.flip_left_right(input_label)
      
    if tf.random.uniform(()) > 0.5:
      # Random mirroring
        input_image = tf.image.rot90(input_image, k = 1)
        input_label = tf.image.rot90(input_label, k = 1)
    
#     print(input_label)
#     print('Hello')
  
    return input_image, input_label

def one_hot(input_image, input_label):
    depth = 2
    input_image = tf.expand_dims(input_image, axis=-1)
    
#     input_label = tf.expand_dims(input_label, axis=-1)
    
    input_label = tf.cast(input_label, dtype = tf.int32)
    input_label = tf.one_hot(input_label, depth)
#     print(input_label)
    return input_image, input_label

import time
EPOCHS = 25
BATCH_SIZE = 10

#initialize arrays early (to avoid local variables being erased)
acc = []
val_acc = []
loss = []
val_loss = []
mean_dice = []
val_mean_dice = []
ivc_dice = []
val_ivc_dice = []
normal_dice = []
val_normal_dice = []
tp = []
fp = []
tn = []
fn = []

model_history = []

#This will run for all batches of data with patches with zeros. It will add the zeros with ones. Th ones are same all the time
for i in range(len(x1_zeros_batches)):
    
    print('Training sub-epoch number is: '+str(i+1))
    
    ##Create train dataset
    x_train = x1_ones
    temp = x1_zeros_batches[i]
    x_train = np.concatenate((x_train, temp), axis = 0)
    
    y_train = y1_ones
    temp = y1_zeros_batches[i]
    y_train = np.concatenate((y_train, temp), axis = 0)
    
    x_train, y_train = shuffle(x_train, y_train, random_state=0)
#     print(x_train.shape)
    
    ##Create validation dataset
    x_test = x2_ones
    temp = x2_zeros_batches[i%len(x2_zeros_batches)] #Since there are less values in test, we retrain on the validation data
    x_test = np.concatenate((x_test, temp), axis = 0)
    
    y_test = y2_ones
    temp = y2_zeros_batches[i%len(x2_zeros_batches)] #Since there are less values in test, we retrain on the validation data
    y_test = np.concatenate((y_test, temp), axis = 0)
    
#     x_test, y_test = shuffle(x_test, y_test, random_state=0)
    
    ''' Expand_dims and One Hot Encoding'''
#     x_train = np.expand_dims(np.asarray(x_train), axis = -1)
#     x_test = np.expand_dims(np.asarray(x_test), axis = -1)
    
#     print(x_train.shape)

#     y_train = to_categorical(np.asarray(y_train))
#     y_test = to_categorical(np.asarray(y_test))
        
    
    # Define data loaders.
    train_loader = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((x_train, y_train))
    validation_loader = tf.data.Dataset.from_tensor_slices((x_test, y_test))
#     print('Tranining')
#     print(train_loader)

    train_dataset = (train_loader.shuffle(len(x_train))
    .map(random_jitter)
    .map(one_hot)
    .batch(BATCH_SIZE)
    .prefetch(2)
    )
    # Only rescale.
    validation_dataset = (validation_loader.shuffle(len(x_test))
    .map(one_hot)
    .batch(BATCH_SIZE)
    .prefetch(2)
    )

    
    ##Start training
    
    iteration_time_start = time.time()
    print('###########')
    local_model_history = model.fit(
        train_dataset,
        validation_data=validation_dataset,
    #    steps_per_epoch=STEPS_PER_EPOCH,
#         batch_size = BATCH_SIZE, 
        epochs = EPOCHS,  
        shuffle=True)
    print("Finished a call to train_model()")
    print("Time for training : "+str(time.time()-iteration_time_start))
    print()
    
    model_history.append(local_model_history)
    
    

#for fivefold, concatenate history of each training into one array
for history in model_history:
    acc = np.concatenate((acc, history.history['accuracy']))
    val_acc = np.concatenate((val_acc, history.history['val_accuracy']))
    loss = np.concatenate((loss, history.history['loss']))
    val_loss = np.concatenate((val_loss, history.history['val_loss']))
    normal_dice = np.concatenate((normal_dice, history.history['normal_dice']))
    val_normal_dice = np.concatenate((val_normal_dice, history.history['val_normal_dice']))
    ivc_dice = np.concatenate((ivc_dice, history.history['ivc_dice']))
    val_ivc_dice = np.concatenate((val_ivc_dice, history.history['val_ivc_dice']))
    mean_dice = np.concatenate((mean_dice, history.history['mean_dice']))
    val_mean_dice = np.concatenate((val_mean_dice, history.history['val_mean_dice']))
    tp = np.concatenate((tp, history.history['tp']))
    fp = np.concatenate((fp, history.history['fp']))
    tn = np.concatenate((tn, history.history['tn']))
    fn = np.concatenate((fn, history.history['fn']))
